Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.
Comment Key: ChronicMedicationList

Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.

------------------------------
Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil
------------------------------
Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Minimal alcohol consumption
Non smoker

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Increased cholesterol and increased waist circumference
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Uric Acid: reduce red meat and keep alcohol intake low
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Special Investigation Notes: Nil
------------------------------
Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal clinical examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Supplement with Vitamin D 3 5000iu daily and repeat bloods in 3 months

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Raised cholesterol
Raised liver enzymes
Mildly raised uric acid
Suboptimal vitamin D
Increased waist circumference
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment

Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels

Comment Value: Increased abdominal adiposity

Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Increased abdominal adiposity

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: EyesightNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Employee: Sechaba Moru

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.
Comment Key: LifestyleNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Uric Acid: reduce red meat and keep alcohol intake low
Comment Key: LifestyleNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.

Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: Cancer has preventable (smoking, alcohol, weight) and non-preventable (genes, age, gender, race) risk factors. Try your best to reduce your risk of preventable factors.
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal clinical examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Women's Health Recommendations:

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Increased cholesterol and increased waist circumference
Comment Key: MentalHealthAnxietyRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: Waist Circumference: reduce saturated fat intake and sugar and improve overall diet whilst maintaining your activity levels.

Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil
------------------------------
Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: No abnormalities detected
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.

Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: MentalHealthStressRecommendation

Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: ReportRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.
Comment Key: SpecialInvestigationRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Uric Acid: reduce red meat and keep alcohol intake low
Comment Key: VitalsNote
Comment Value: Increased waist circumference and WHtR% means incr risk for chronic diseases of lifestyle
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.
Comment Key: VitalsNote
Comment Value: Increased waist circumference and WHtR% means incr risk for chronic diseases of lifestyle
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Increased cholesterol and increased waist circumference
Comment Key: VitalsRecommendation
Comment Value: None

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Liver enzymes: reduce any unnecessary medicine intake and keep alcohol consumption low. Losing abdominal fat and cutting out sugar may also help to reduce these enzymes.
Comment Key: VitaminsOrSupplements
Comment Value: Vitamin D , Vitamin B co
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

------------------------------
Employee: Sechaba Moru
Report Date: 2020-09-29
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal clinical examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: to try manage with lifestyle only. Take omega 3 supplements 2g daily and eat a mediterranean style diet as discussed. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Minimal alcohol consumption
Non smoker
Regular exercise
Comment Key: WomensHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Increased cholesterol and increased waist circumference
Comment Key: WomensHealthRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil
